# 4. Outlier Detection

## Definition

Outliers are unusually large or small values.

Example:

Most salaries:

₹30,000 – ₹100,000

One salary:

₹5,000,000

This record may distort learning.

---

## Common Detection Methods

* Box Plot
* IQR Method
* Z-Score

---

# 5. Data Normalization

## Definition

Rescaling values into a fixed range.

Usually:

0 to 1

---

## Formula

x_normalized

=

(x − min)

/

(max − min)

---

## Example

Age:

20

40

60

Normalized:

0

0.5

1

---

# 6. Standardization

## Definition

Transforming data so it has:

Mean = 0

Standard Deviation = 1

---

## Formula

Standardized Value

=

(x − Mean)

/

Standard Deviation

---

## Example

Used in:

Customer Segmentation Project

Before K-Means Clustering

---

# Why Scaling Matters

Without scaling:

Income = 100000

Age = 25

Income dominates learning.

After scaling:

Income and Age contribute equally.

